byline.contributor: Falih Hassan, Omar al-Jawoshy and Ahmed Salah contributed reporting.

lead_paragraph: Many of the Iraqis who joined Syrians, Africans and Afghans in the great migrant wave to Europe last year with expectations of quick success are now turning around.

headline.print_headline: Iraqi Migrants Leaving Europe, Dreams Unmet
headline.main: Disappointed With Europe, Thousands of Iraqi Migrants Return Home

snippet: Many of the Iraqis who joined Syrians, Africans and Afghans in the great migrant wave to Europe last year with expectations of quick success are now turning around.
abstract: Thousands of Iraqi migrants are leaving Europe and returning home, chagrined over lack of success in starting new, prosperous lives; joining in great migrant wave, traveling through Turkey to Continent, some say they had unrealistic expectations and were treated suspiciously in wake of Paris terrorist attacks.
